{"comments":"Interpolation Types — ADTs for stroke interpolation and dab spacing.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nStroke interpolation transforms discrete input points into smooth brush\nstrokes. The interpolation method determines curve quality, while spacing\nmode controls how dabs are placed along the interpolated path.\n\n## Interpolation Method\n\nCurve algorithm for smoothing input points:\n\n- **Linear**: Straight lines, fastest but angular\n- **Catmull**: Catmull-Rom spline, smooth and natural\n- **Bezier**: Cubic Bezier, precise control\n- **BSpline**: B-spline, smoother than Catmull\n- **Hermite**: Hermite spline with velocity tangents\n\n## Spacing Mode\n\nHow dabs are distributed along the stroke:\n\n- **AbsolutePixels**: Fixed pixel distance (e.g., 5px)\n- **PercentOfDiameter**: Relative to brush size (e.g., 25%)\n- **Adaptive**: Adjusts based on velocity\n- **AutoDensity**: Algorithm-determined optimal spacing\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[92,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Interpolation/Types.purs","start":[92,3]},"title":"Linear"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[93,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Interpolation/Types.purs","start":[93,3]},"title":"Catmull"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[94,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Interpolation/Types.purs","start":[94,3]},"title":"Bezier"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[95,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Interpolation/Types.purs","start":[95,3]},"title":"BSpline"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[96,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Interpolation/Types.purs",